article.headline: UAB 79, Louisiana Tech 67
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) -- DeMario Eddins and Ronell Taylor combined for 27 points, 26 coming in the second half, as UAB defeated Louisiana Tech 79-67 Tuesday night. The game was tied 45-45 early in the second half before UAB went on a 17-0 run to take control. Eddins and Taylor scored 7 points each to spark the decisive run. UAB (6-2) got 12 points from Gabe Kennedy while Donell Taylor had 9 points and five steals. The Blazers used pressure defense to force 23 turnovers, 13 coming in the second half. Paul Millsaps led Louisiana Tech (4-4) with 17 points and 10 rebounds. JueMichael Young added 12 points and Corey Dean had 10. Louisiana Tech was a decided underdog coming into the game, but the Bulldogs outrebounded UAB 29-28 on their way to a 35-34 halftime lead. UAB hurt itself by making only 6 of 16 free throws in the first half. Louisiana Tech grabbed four 3-point leads early in the second half. Wayne Powell scored three-straight baskets inside to help Louisiana Tech offset UAB's defensive pressure. Ronell Taylor promptly scored a layup off a steal to start the 17-0 run. The Blazers went on to lead by as many as 19 points before Tech cut the margin late.
